'''Kohlit''' is a place, possibly a hill, mentioned several times in the [[Copper Scroll]], one of the [[Dead Sea Scrolls]].  Kohlit has become something of a modern-day [[El Dorado (myth)|El Dorado]].

It is the area given where the second Copper Scroll, containing a more detailed list, is buried.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jewishchristianlit.com/Texts/StudTxts/3Q15.html#fn6|title=Hack & Carey: The Copper Scroll: 3Q15|publisher=|date=November 23, 1998|accessdate=17 April 2017}}</ref>

Kohlit is also an area east of the Jordan River where [[Alexander Jannaeus]] had military campaigns. It is unknown whether this is the same Kohlit as the city.

